> Bored with brunch? That's why we're bringing you this epic brunch board! It's got all the box office hits, the numero unos, the crème de la crèmes: churro-style waffles (that's crispy, sweet, and cinnamony to you!) with an extra crisp and smoky bacon topper. There's also scallion-studded scrambled eggs sprinkled with Parmesan, juicy cinnamon sugar-sprinkled orange slices, and a luscious maple syrup sauce swirled with crème fraîche to drizzle over everything. If that doesn't get you and yours out of bed, we don't know what will!

Heat a large dry, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%ounce}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop.

Let pan cool, carefully discard bacon fat, then wash out pan.

While bacon cooks, wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Halve @orange{1}; cut into thin wedges (we got eight wedges per orange).

In a #medium bowl{}, whisk together @eggs{4}, half the @crème fraîche{2%tablespoon}, @water{2%TBSP} (4 TBSP for 4 servings), a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}. Set aside.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, heat @maple syrup{2%tablespoon} until warm, ~{30-60%seconds}. Whisk in remaining @crème fraîche{2%tablespoon} and @water{2%tsp} (4 tsp for 4) until smooth.

In a second medium bowl, combine @cinnamon{1%teaspoon} and @sugar{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4 servings).

Toast @Belgian waffle{2} until golden brown.

Immediately add hot waffles to bowl with cinnamon sugar, tossing to fully coat. (Reserve any remaining cinnamon sugar for Step 6.)

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in pan used for bacon over medium heat. Add scallion whites. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in egg mixture; cook, undisturbed, until just set, ~{30-45%seconds}. Continue to cook, gently stirring in a figure-eight pattern, until curds form and eggs are scrambled to preference.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Transfer scrambled eggs to a #serving plate{} and sprinkle with @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon} and as many scallion greens as you like.

Transfer waffles to a second serving plate and top with creamy maple sauce and chopped bacon. Shingle orange slices on a third serving plate and sprinkle with any remaining cinnamon sugar. Serve family style.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

> Wash hands and surfaces after handling raw eggs. Consuming raw or undercooked eggs may increase your risk of foodborne illness.